    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix integer truncation in F1AP to_NRNRB function\n\n### Summary\nThe `to_NRNRB` function in F1AP interface management was causing integer truncation when its return value was assigned to the ENUMERATED `nRNRB` field in ASN.1 structures. The function returned an `int` type while the target field expects a smaller integer type, leading to potential data loss.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_interface_management.c`: \n  - Changed return type of `to_NRNRB` from `int` to `uint8_t`\n  - Added `#include <stdint.h>` for `uint8_t` definition\n  - Added explicit return statement after `AssertFatal` to satisfy compiler requirements\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen processing F1AP Setup Request messages with specific transmission bandwidth configurations, the gNB-DU may experience unexpected behavior during the encoding of Served Cell Information. The `nRNRB` field in the ASN.1 structures may receive truncated values, leading to incorrect bandwidth configuration being sent to the gNB-CU.\n\nSymptoms include:\n- F1AP Setup Request failures\n- Incorrect cell configuration reporting\n- Potential connection establishment issues with UEs\n\nThe issue is particularly noticeable when using transmission bandwidths with higher NRB values from the lookup table, where the truncation is more likely to occur.\n"
}